The paper discusses the current state and future perspectives of machine learning for robotic behaviors, focusing on complex robots such as humanoid robots or legged robots. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), specifically machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for sensorially complex robots. The paper also discusses the integration of classical robotics and other approaches from artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
